# Clear the plate entry on the loading tray without moving any motor.
#
# Called by an orchestrating client after an EXTERNAL actor physically
# removes the plate from the Liconic transfer tray — e.g. the Hamilton
# iSWAP picking up from the incubator handoff in a workcell round-trip.
# The Liconic has no way to detect that event on its own, so the client
# must explicitly tell the registry.
#
# Returns the plate_name that was removed, or "" if the tray was
# already empty. Always success=true unless an unexpected error occurs.
---
bool success
string message
string cleared_plate_name
